NBA FINALS: CAVALIERS v SPURS
June 13, 2007
Sasha Pavlovic
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
  Q.  You spent one year in University before playing --   
 SASHA PAVLOVIC:  I've never been in America before I came to the NBA.   
  
  Q.  I read something.  You played one year in your league, no?   
 SASHA PAVLOVIC:  Yeah.   
  
  Q.  So it's a big experience for you?   
 SASHA PAVLOVIC:  Yeah, it was a big experience before coming to the NBA.   
  
  Q.  Your first year in Utah, it was not so easy?   
 SASHA PAVLOVIC:  No, it was hard, but I had several friends that were there that helped me a lot.   
  
  Q.  In Cleveland you had a difficult beginning, also?   
 SASHA PAVLOVIC:  No, I don't think so.  When I came to Cleveland I was already in the NBA and I knew what to expect.   
  
  Q.  You made a lot of progress in defense recently, no?   
 SASHA PAVLOVIC:  Yeah, coach wanted me to do that in order to play, so I worked hard this summer and worked on my legs, and I came back at it.   
   
